🔥 1) ORC – disparar pipeline completo

Endpoint:

POST http://localhost:8000/orc/start


Body:

{
  "vendor": "postgres",
  "dataset": "customer_churn",
  "query": ""
}


Isso dispara toda a pipeline:

Gera trace-id

Chama DCP

Chama EDA

Chama ML

Retorna tudo agregado

🔥 2) DCP – testar ingestão isolada

Endpoint:

POST http://autosage-dcp:8001/start


Body:

{
  "data": {
    "vendor": "postgres",
    "dataset": "customer_churn",
    "query": ""
  }
}


O DCP vai gerar:

/registry/dcp/customer_churn/v0001.parquet

🔥 3) EDA – testar EDA isolado

Pega o artefato gerado pelo DCP, por exemplo:

/registry/dcp/customer_churn/customer_churn_v0001.parquet


Endpoint:

POST http://autosage-eda:8002/eda/run


Body:

{
  "trace_id": "123456789",
  "data": {
    "artifact_path": "/registry/dcp/customer_churn/customer_churn_v0001.parquet"
  }
}


Retorno esperado:

/registry/eda/customer_churn/customer_churn_v0001.parquet

🔥 4) ML – testar ML isolado

Pega o artefato retornado pela EDA:

/registry/eda/customer_churn/customer_churn_v0001.parquet


Endpoint:

POST http://autosage-ml:8003/internal/run


Body:

{
  "trace_id": "123456789",
  "data": {
    "artifact_path": "/registry/eda/customer_churn/customer_churn_v0001.parquet",
    "task_name": "classification",
    "parameters": {}
  }
}


Retorno esperado:

{
  "success": true,
  "trace_id": "123456789",
  "data": {
    "processed_files": [
      "/registry/ml/processed/customer_churn_clean.csv"
    ]
  },
  "error": null
}

🔥 5) Request para testar ML com target manual
{
  "trace_id": "abc-123",
  "data": {
    "artifact_path": "/registry/eda/customer_churn/customer_churn_v0002.parquet",
    "task_name": "classification",
    "parameters": {
      "target": "Churn"
    }
  }
}

